                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Amiranian/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-06T09:00:00+03:25"
                            >June 6, 1938—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 6—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>62. I learn from a source close to the Palace that when the decision of the
                    company was communicated to the Shah the latter merely remarked “so much the
                    better” and has not referred to it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
